\n<Mitch>The deer guy- I mean, Mr. Lane boiled a kettle so I can get up the ladder in the garden.
\n<Mitch>I'm almost out of here, but... Uh...
\n<Mitch>Do you want to... come with me?
\n<Caroline>\fi\oc[5]But, I can't leave. This library's been my home for a long time.
\n<Caroline>\fi\oc[5]You need to get out of here and go back to YOUR home, got it?
\n<Caroline>\fi\oc[5]A certain somebody is throwing a tantrum because you got all the library cards.
\n<Caroline>\fi\oc[5]She liked making stupid games and stuff for me and Miss Christine to try out, but...
\n<Caroline>\fi\oc[5]Look, you need to get as far away from the library as possible.
\n<Mitch>Ugh... I'd say no to the star when she'd whine about it. I'd stop playing when she "wasn't having fun losing"...
\n<Mitch>Never went near this place since she got killed in the parking lot and of course the one time I do, she's back to making a show out of drowning while holding my head under.
\n<Caroline>\fi\oc[5]I don't know if she's still in there ripping tiles off the wall, but you should still get out of here before she treats you like one.
\n<Mitch>Thanks, but if she wants to confront me before I make it out of here, I want to see her.
\n<Caroline>\fi\oc[5]I don't know the whole story, but you better survive this crazy ass idea of yours.
\n<Caroline>\fi\oc[5]By the way, did you do anything to piss off Mr. Malthus?
\n<Caroline>\fi\oc[5]The tall guy with the television static. The one you were afraid of before.
\n<Mitch>Ugh, no clue. He came out of the payphone when I tried to use it.
\n<Mitch>That was around when I just got here... I think.
\n<Caroline>\fi\oc[5]Don't worry, it's not hard to upset him.
\n<Mitch>I think that's a big thing to worry about.
\n<Caroline>\fi\oc[5]No, I mean he finds something to hate about every visitor.
\n<Caroline>\fi\oc[5]Seems really keen on straight up killing you, though.
\n<Caroline>\fi\oc[5]For all we know, he just wants your scarf.
